</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

</OperationDescriptionSection>

  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.list({});

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();`}

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.list()

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

async function run() {

```python
from mistralai import Mistral


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\} \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTitle slot="title">

### Code Samples \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append+code-samples\}

TypeScript

<SectionContent
  slot="content"

>

<TryItNow
  externalDependencies={{"zod":"^3.25.64","@mistralai/mistralai":"latest"}}
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.append({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationAppendRequest: {
      inputs: [
        {
          object: "entry",
          type: "message.input",
          role: "user",
          content: [
            {
              documentUrl: "https://oblong-decryption.info/",
              type: "document_url",
            },
          ],
        },
      ],
    },
  });

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append+code-samples+python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral, models


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[
        {
            "object": models.MessageInputEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.MessageInputEntryType.MESSAGE_INPUT,
            "role": models.MessageInputEntryRole.USER,
            "content": [
                {
                    "document_url": "https://oblong-decryption.info/",
                    "type": models.DocumentURLChunkType.DOCUMENT_URL,
                },
            ],
        },
    ])

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/history \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_history\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all entries in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the entries belonging to that conversation. The entries are sorted in the order they were appended, those can be messages, connectors or function_call.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",

```python
from mistralai import Mistral

    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_history(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>GET</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/messages \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_messages\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Retrieve all messages in a conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id retrieve all the messages belonging to that conversation. This is similar to retrieving all entries except we filter the messages only.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.getMessages({

```python
from mistralai import Mistral

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.get_messages(conversation_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTitle slot="title">

### Code Samples \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart+code-samples\}

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart+code-samples+typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  externalDependencies={{"zod":"^3.25.64","@mistralai/mistralai":"latest"}}
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restart({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationRestartRequest: {
      inputs: "<value>",
      fromEntryId: "<id>",
    },
  });

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();`}
/>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>", from_entry_id="<id>")

    # Handle response
    print(res)
```

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Create a conversation and append entries to it._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Create a new conversation, using a base model or an agent and append entries. Completion and tool executions are run and the response is appended to the conversation.Use the returned conversation_id to continue the conversation.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTitle slot="title">

### Code Samples \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream+code-samples\}

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"

>

<TryItNow
  externalDependencies={{"zod":"^3.25.64","@mistralai/mistralai":"latest"}}
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.startStream({
    inputs: [
      {
        object: "entry",
        type: "function.result",
        toolCallId: "<id>",
        result: "<value>",
      },
      {
        object: "entry",
        type: "message.input",
        role: "user",
        content: "<value>",
      },
      {
        object: "entry",
        type: "message.input",
        role: "user",
        content: "<value>",
      },
    ],
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream+code-samples+python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_start_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral, models


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.start_stream(inputs=[
        {
            "object": models.FunctionResultEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.FunctionResultEntryType.FUNCTION_RESULT,
            "tool_call_id": "<id>",
            "result": "<value>",
        },
        {
            "object": models.MessageInputEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.MessageInputEntryType.MESSAGE_INPUT,
            "role": models.MessageInputEntryRole.USER,
            "content": "<value>",
        },
        {
            "object": models.MessageInputEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.MessageInputEntryType.MESSAGE_INPUT,
            "role": models.MessageInputEntryRole.USER,
            "content": "<value>",
        },
    ])

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)
```

</CodeSample>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Append new entries to an existing conversation._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Run completion on the history of the conversation and the user entries. Return the new created entries.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTitle slot="title">

### Code Samples \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples\}

</SectionTitle>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples+typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples+typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  externalDependencies={{"zod":"^3.25.64","@mistralai/mistralai":"latest"}}
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.appendStream({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationAppendStreamRequest: {
      inputs: "<value>",
    },
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples+python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_append_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.append_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs="<value>")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)
```

</CodeSample>

</SectionContent>

<OperationTitleSection slot="title">

## <Pill variant="primary"><b>POST</b></Pill> /v1/conversations/\{conversation\_id\}/restart\#stream \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream\}

</OperationTitleSection>

<OperationSummarySection slot="summary">

_Restart a conversation starting from a given entry._

</OperationSummarySection>

<OperationDescriptionSection slot="description">

Given a conversation_id and an id, recreate a conversation from this point and run completion. A new conversation is returned with the new entries returned.

</OperationDescriptionSection>

<OperationCodeSamplesSection slot="code-samples">

<TabbedSection>

<SectionTitle slot="title">

### Code Samples \{#operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples\}

</SectionTitle>

  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples+typescript"
>

TypeScript

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples+typescript"
>

<TryItNow
  externalDependencies={{"zod":"^3.25.64","@mistralai/mistralai":"latest"}}
  defaultValue={`import { Mistral } from "@mistralai/mistralai";

const mistral = new Mistral({
  apiKey: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await mistral.beta.conversations.restartStream({
    conversationId: "<id>",
    conversationRestartStreamRequest: {
      inputs: [
        {
          object: "entry",
          type: "message.input",
          role: "assistant",
          content: "<value>",
        },
        {
          object: "entry",
          type: "message.input",
          role: "assistant",
          content: "<value>",
        },
      ],
      fromEntryId: "<id>",
    },
  });

  for await (const event of result) {
    // Handle the event
    console.log(event);
  }
}

run();`}
/>

</SectionContent>

<SectionTab
  slot="tab"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples+python"
>

Python

</SectionTab>

<SectionContent
  slot="content"
  id="operation-agents_api_v1_conversations_restart_stream+code-samples+python"
>

<CodeSample>

```python
from mistralai import Mistral, models


with Mistral(
    api_key="<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
) as mistral:

    res = mistral.beta.conversations.restart_stream(conversation_id="<id>", inputs=[
        {
            "object": models.MessageInputEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.MessageInputEntryType.MESSAGE_INPUT,
            "role": models.MessageInputEntryRole.ASSISTANT,
            "content": "<value>",
        },
        {
            "object": models.MessageInputEntryObject.ENTRY,
            "type": models.MessageInputEntryType.MESSAGE_INPUT,
            "role": models.MessageInputEntryRole.ASSISTANT,
            "content": "<value>",
        },
    ], from_entry_id="<id>")

    with res as event_stream:
        for event in event_stream:
            # handle event
            print(event, flush=True)
```

</CodeSample>
